<title>GERMANY: German plant, equipment sector to cut 10,000 jobs.</title>
<headline>German plant, equipment sector to cut 10,000 jobs.</headline>
<dateline>STUTTGART, Germany 1997-02-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Germany's plant and mechanical engineering industry will shed 10,000 jobs, or about one percent of its workforce, in 1997 but said job losses will end this year, the VDMA industry association said.</p>
<p>VDMA president Michael Rogowski told a news conference that the sector would only be able to increase employment if it grew at a rate of three to four percent for a long period.  </p>
<p>The VDMA last month predicted output growth of three percent in 1997, up from one percent growth in 1996.</p>
<p>&quot;We expect that the job losses will come to a standstill in the course of 1997,&quot; Rogowski said.</p>
